  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'What is the variance of a dataset?', 'The average of the squared differences from the mean', 'The square root of the standard deviation', 'The average of the absolute differences from the mean', 'The difference between maximum and minimum', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'In probability, two events A and B are independent if:', 'P(A and B) = P(A) * P(B)', 'P(A and B) = P(A) + P(B)', 'P(A|B) = P(B)', 'P(A and B) = 0', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'The gradient of a function is a vector that points in the direction of:', 'Maximum increase', 'Maximum decrease', 'No change', 'Minimum value', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'What is the eigenvalue of a matrix A if there exists a non-zero vector v such that Av = λv?', 'λ is the eigenvalue', 'v is the eigenvalue', 'λ is the eigenvector', 'A is the eigenvalue', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'The mean of a standard normal distribution is:', '0', '1', '0.5', 'Depends on data', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'The integral of a probability density function over its entire domain is:', '1', '0', 'Infinity', 'Depends on distribution', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'In linear regression, the method of least squares minimizes:', 'The sum of squared errors', 'The sum of absolute errors', 'The sum of errors', 'The maximum error', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'What is the rank of a matrix?', 'The number of linearly independent rows or columns', 'The number of non-zero rows', 'The determinant of the matrix', 'The trace of the matrix', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'The chain rule in calculus is used to:', 'Differentiate composite functions', 'Integrate products', 'Find limits', 'Solve differential equations', NULL, true),
  ('846bb4e7-894e-4946-9074-e7534ddae770', 'In probability, what is the expectation of a random variable X?', 'The weighted average of all possible values', 'The most likely value', 'The median', 'The variance', NULL, true),
